==Ladder== All teams played 20 games during the home and away season, for a total of 165. Each team also had two [[bye (sports)|byes]]. An additional 7 games were played during the finals series.
{{AFL Ladder/1993}}
==Awards== *The [[Brownlow Medal]] was awarded to [[Gavin Wanganeen]] of {{AFL Ess}}. *The [[Leigh Matthews Trophy|AFLPA MVP]] was awarded to [[Gary Ablett, Sr.|Gary Ablett]] of {{AFL Gee}}. *The [[Coleman Medal]] was awarded to [[Gary Ablett, Sr.|Gary Ablett]] of {{AFL Gee}}. *The [[Norm Smith Medal]] was awarded to [[Michael Long (footballer)|Michael Long]] of {{AFL Ess}}. *The inaugural [[AFL Rising Star]] award was awarded to [[Nathan Buckley]] of {{AFL BB}}. *The [[Wooden Spoon (award)|Wooden Spoon]] was "awarded" to {{AFL Syd}}.
==Notable events== * {{AFL Nor}} and {{AFL BB}} both set club-record high scores in this season. North Melbourne's 35.19 (229) in round 6 was the fifth-highest score of all time, and Brisbane's 33.21 (219) was the tenth-highest of all times. The opponent in both of these games was {{AFL Syd}}. * In the same game, {{AFL BB}} set the record for the highest score at three-quarter time, 27.17 (179). This remained the record until [[2007 AFL season|2007]].
